# Maintainer-only merges

Only repository maintainers merge pull requests and push release tags.

## Automation must not

- Run `gh pr merge` (any mode) or `gh pr review --approve`
- Merge via GitHub API or other tooling
- Push release tags (`git push origin v*`) unless a maintainer explicitly
  requests that exact tag in the same message
- Force-push or rewrite shared branch history without maintainer approval

## Required workflow

1. Branch → commit → push branch
2. Open a PR when requested
3. Stop — return the PR URL; maintainer reviews and merges
4. Continue follow-up work only after the maintainer confirms merge or next step

## Releases

Do not tag or publish as a follow-up to opening a PR. Tag and publish only when
a maintainer explicitly requests it in that message.
